result.execSummary:
The defendant Nathan R Walters was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Nathan R Walters is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Nathan R Walters was found guilty of 3rd Degree Sexual Assault, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3).
  • Nathan R Walters was found guilty of Manufacture/Deliver THC (<=200g) [Modifiers: Possession with Intent to Deliver/Distribute a Controlled Substance On or Near a School], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(h)1.
  • Nathan R Walters was found guilty of Manufacture/Deliver THC (<=200g), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(h)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: If probation or extended supervision is revoked or will discharge with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.

Defendant shall not possess or consume alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription. 
Defendant shall not associate with known drug users or dealers or be present where drugs are illegally purchased, sold or consumed. 
Defendant shall not enter any establishment where the primary purpose is the sale or service of alcohol. 
Defendant shall not have direct or indirect contact with NMF (dob 3-4-00) or her residence, family or school.
Defendant shall not have contact with females under age 18 without prior agent approval.

Defendant shall participate in an AODA assessment, sex offender treatment and all counseling or treatment programs as directed by his supervising agent. 
Defendant shall provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis.  Defendant has the right to request expungement of DNA analysis in writing through the Department of Justice.
Defendant shall comply with sex offender registration requirements.
Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.
Defendant shall pay Dept of Corrections supervision fees.
